title: Americans Flock to Vote Early as Hints Emerge of Republican Strength
description: Turnout is high in most states, and experts see broad Republican energy as well as Democratic enthusiasm in major battlegrounds. But changes in how people vote have added new uncertainty.
dc:creator: Nick Corasaniti
media:credit: Taylor Glascock for The New York Times
media:description: Voters left after casting early ballots on Wednesday in Kenosha, Wis. Since the beginning of the pandemic, far more Americans now cast their ballots early or by mail.
